<br>
She senses someone approaching her and she looks up slowly and sees the barmaid standing there.<br>
<br>
&quot;And what can I get for you?&quot;  The barmaid seemed impatient with her and Chessie notices her looking over in the other darkened corner at some creepy looking guy in a dark cloak that seems to know that Chessie was glancing at him.<br>
<br>
&quot;I..I..would like a glass of water,&quot; Chessie stammered in a barely audible whisper.<br>
<br>
&quot;What was that?&quot;  The barmaid leans closer to try to hear Chessie.<br>
<br>
&quot;Water...I..would like a glass of water,&quot; Chessie dropped her eyes to the table again, her voice wavering as she tried to speak louder.<br>
<br>
The barmaid pondered for a moment at what was wrong with this girl.<br>
<br>
&quot;Sure thing&quot;  The barmaid walked off to get some water.  Chessie peaked again at the dark cloaked guy in the corner out of the corner of her eyes and she knew without a doubt he knew that she was looking at him again.  She shuddered and wished she could disappear.<br>
<br>
The barmaid returned with her water and placed it in front of her.<br>
<br>
&quot;Are you okey?&quot; Chessie looked up and nodded slowly. &quot;Whats wrong?  The bar isn't too busy, if you need to talk let me know ok?&quot;  Chessie nodded again.  She watched the barmaid walk to another corner of the room and talk to a pale skinned person in a robe.<br>
<br>
She took a drink of water and it felt good on her throat.  She wished she had the nerve to be more social, for her life had been mostly solitary.  She thought back to her mother who had taken care of her for her father had passed away when she was very young.  Her mother was her only friend and only companion she had known.  She grew up in Everfrost Peaks, out on the plains.  She knew other barbarians lived in the town of Halas, but she had never been there until her mother sent her to the church.  Her mother was a missionary of sorts, and helped travelers who ventured into Everfrost with food, healing, money if needed.  Chessie had an argument with her mother once and ran away.  She planned on going to Halas, and approached the cave that lead to the town cautiously.  She ran into some young barbarians who were hanging outside of the cave.  She smiled at them as she walked towards them.  They continued to look at her without emotion on their face.<br>
<br>
&quot;Do you need more water?&quot;  Chessie gasped as she heard a voice.  She jumped a bit in her chair and bumped the table and knocked her glass over onto the floor where it broke into small pieces. <br>
<br>
&quot;Sorry, I'm so sorry.&quot;  Chessie said.  She stood up and tried to pick up the pieces off the floor.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hey its ok!  A little broken glass is nothing!&quot; The good hearted barmaid smiled.  A broom was quickly produced and the glass swept up.<br>
<br>
&quot;You looked like you were in another world.&quot;  Chessie sat back down.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes I was thinking of ....well..I was thinking of something.&quot;  Chessie realized she had said too much.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, the Hero Heart Tavern is a good place to relax and meet new people.  Why don't you stay awhile, and maybe later we can talk more.&quot;  Chessie studied the barmaids face and saw nothing more than a friendly and somewhat concerned expression.<br>
<br>
Chessie nodded.  Suddenly the door opened and in walked some people.<br>
<br>
