<br>
Sadly she watched her muffin being eaten by someone else at the bar.  Several people have come and went and she had taken notice of them all, wishing she had enough courage to be more friendly, but she was tired.  Lonely, sad and tired; in her bones, in her heart, in her soul.<br>
<br>
She notices that the strange man in the dark robes suddenly stand up and a muffled cry came up out of her throat when she directed her eyes towards the door and saw another man enter.<br>
<br>
Suddenly an overwhelming sense of vertigo overtakes her and she falls out of her chair and onto the floor.  Her last thoughts were &quot;Maybe its time to join me mam.&quot;<br>
