<br>
She noticed the young girl come into the tavern, and continued on with her thoughts; another local villager no doubt, trying to woo the local soldier with her giggles.  Why meddle in the affairs of fools?  A muffled cry from the cloaked female draws her attention again however, as instincts kick in.<br>
<br>
&quot;Surely there is more than I had thought to this girl&quot; she thinks after a moment of hesitation.<br>
<br>
Under the guise of drinking her ale, she shifts her weight so that her body turns to the girl, careful to appear focused elsewhere.  No sooner than she does, the female cries out as in pain, her glass shattering on the broken wood floor.  She watches the barmaid console the girl, trying in vain to make idle talk.  What could scare such a young soul?  A griffon?  Perhaps a close call with a Hill Giant? <br>
<br>
The hair on Robertz neck rise as she follows the frightened stares of the girl into the corner of the dark bar; to a cloaked person.   <br>
<br>
&quot;Male, obviously&quot; she thinks to herself somewhat scoffing under her breath. &quot;The boots are to wide for a female, and the cloak falls on shoulders much too broad. not to mention the stench of death on his neglected blade, sheathed yet encrusted with human blood....for abusing a blade like that alone is enough reason to kill him&quot;  She stops, startled, and quickly calms her face into a mask of nothingness again.  &quot;How...&quot; Her mind races to comprehend how she knew of the blade, still sheathed, forgetting the girl for a moment.  Then she relaxes, as it dawns on her. &quot;The new powers of course...&quot;   The cries from the girl startle Robertz from her throughts again as she falls to the floor, swooning with delerium.  Her eyes follow the girls terrified gaze as she falls, leading to the tavern's newest arrival.  The barmaid steps in catching the girl, and obscuring her view of the new patron.  The customers whisper among themselves, headless tales and gossip surely.   Seeing the girl carried through the doorway, Robertz decides to follow...after relieving the cloaked man of his sword and purse;  A child's task with the liquor he had consumed that night.  <br>
<br>
